类 JacketMenu

java.lang.Object
org.kelvinizer.support.classes.JacketMenu
public class JacketMenu extends Object
This class is a menu that stores a list of Pair objects with a String name and a BufferedImage jacket. It is used in the selection of collections and songs.

      public void moveBackward()
      Move the menu backwards. This means decrementing the value of menuIndex by 1 if menuIndex is not already at 0

    • moveForward

      public void moveForward()
      Move the menu forward. This means incrementing the value of menuIndex by 1 if menuIndex is not already at menu.size()-1

    • move
